Ireland’s NAMA to Sell Two U.K. Debt Portfolios, Times Says

-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 
2011-10-09T11:14:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/ireland-s-nama-to-sell-two-u-k-debt-portfolios-times-says.html
Ireland’s National Asset Management
Agency appointed agents to handle the sale of the equivalent of
800 million euros ($1.1 billion) of U.K. real-estate loans, the
 Sunday Times  said, without citing anyone.  The state-owned company hired Savills Plc and CB Richard
Ellis Inc. to sell the two portfolios, the newspaper said. NAMA
 said  on Sept. 29 it is seeking advisers to help sell its
European and U.S. loans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joe Brennan in Dublin at 
 jbrennan29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  